&lt;h2 id="intro">Intro
&lt;/h2>&lt;p>Installing in a VM, using Fedora&amp;rsquo;s &lt;em>Boxes&lt;/em> software.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="pre-install-setup">Pre-install Setup
&lt;/h2>&lt;h3 id="download-image">Download Image
&lt;/h3>&lt;p>Grab it from the
&lt;a class="link" href="https://archlinux.org/download/"
target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>
official download page
&lt;/a>
. BT download is recommended (use a proper torrent client, like
&lt;a class="link" href="https://www.qbittorrent.org/"
target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>
qBittorrent
&lt;/a>
).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Then drop it into your VM.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="verify-boot-mode">Verify Boot Mode
&lt;/h3>&lt;p>List the efivars directory:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">ls /sys/firmware/efi/efivars
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>If the directory shows up correctly with no errors, your system is booting in UEFI mode. If it&amp;rsquo;s missing, you&amp;rsquo;re likely in
&lt;a class="link" href="https://zh.wikipedia.org/wiki/BIOS"
target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>
BIOS
&lt;/a>
mode (or CSM mode).&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>